    "body": "@OmarBasem yeah, I am aware of what causes the \"issue\", I mentioned it on Discord, also Andrey commented on the original issue [here](https://github.com/status-im/status-mobile/issues/15346#issuecomment-1468565298) (we may have picked the wrong word for the safe area though).\r\n\r\nAnd you're actually right, my point was that it just doesn't look pretty in comparison with iOS :) Because, as already mentioned, it has that safe area, thanks to which the composer looks more proportionate on iOS devices.\r\n\r\nAnd that's why Andrey and I thought that it could be fixed, and he added some additional padding for Android, which later was removed after the introduction of the new composer.\r\n\r\nHowever, you also have a good point about iPhone SE which has a physical button, the composer really looks the same on it.\r\n\r\nSo I suggest not focusing on this, within 1.23, and closing the issue. In the meantime, I'll ask what the designers think about this, and maybe we'll come back to this question later.\r\n\r\nThanks for looking into this carefully and for the detailed explanation! 🙏",
